<div class='pages-carousel__image' style='background-image:url(//pb-assets.tedcdn.com/system/baubles/files/000/003/029/original/TEDBooks_Why_We_Love_carousel_book.jpg?1441205124);'></div>
<div class='pages-carousel__content inverse module'>
<a class='pages-carousel__heading' href='/read/ted-books/ted-books-library/why-we-work'>Why We Work</a>
<div class='pages-carousel__text'>
<div class='pages-carousel__body'>
<p>In this groundbreaking work, acclaimed writer and thinker Barry Schwartz dispels a deeply ingrained myth: The reason we work is primarily to get a paycheck. </p>

</div>
</div>
<div class='pages-carousel__credit'>Barry Schwartz</div>
<a class='pages-carousel__link button button--dark' href='/read/ted-books/ted-books-library/why-we-work'>Learn more</a>
